definition.value: A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is oleanane containing a double bond between positions 12 and 13 and substituted by hydroxy groups at the 3beta, 22beta and 24-positions.

A triterpenoid saponin that is composed of soyasapogenol B having an alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranosiduronic acid moiety attached at the 3-position via a glycosidic linkage.

A member of the class of benzothiazoles that is 1,3-benzothiazole-4,7-dione substituted by methyl and (4-methylphenyl)amino groups at positions 2 and 5, respectively. It is an inhibitor of CDK4 and SETD8 and exhibits cytotoxicity towards a number of human cancer cell lines.
